caption: The sandwiches were big and delicious! The waffle fries were tasty as were the risotto balls.

I ordered through Doordash yesterday. I got a turkey sub and for some reason some type of meat was added to it. Not sure what is was, but I don't eat red meat or pork. I just took it off, no problem, but the wheat bread was hard as a rock and skinned the roof of my mouth. Furthermore, my son said his chicken cheesesteak was nasty. I like Doordash, because I find restaurants I've never heard of, but this is my first and last time ordering from this location.
I didn't care for the beef and kale sandwich at all. The bread was tough to chew, the meat had lots of tendon and vein, and the overall flavor was just off.

Ordered the Benny (breaded chicken, no pork) but they gave me the Rizzo, which had big pieces of prosciutto all inside, and I do not eat pork due to my dietary restrictions and so I asked them to make me another one and only 2 minutes later, they gave me thr same sandwich without the prosciutto. I don't believe they remade it because the Benny does not have the honey sauce on it and the sandwich i ate had it. Pretty dissatisfied that they didn't even say sorry and then didn't even remake my sandwich. Not coming here again.
The Special Philly was great, good chili cheakpea and waffle fries
Excellent.  This is the tastiest quick meal on the Wharf.  Yummmmm..... breaded cutlet,  not grilled chicken
I’d put Grazie Grazie’s Italian sandwiches up against any deli in NYC or jersey
Delicious sandwiches!
Holy cow, great cheesesteaks. I can’t wait to try the rest of the menu!
Dang, them's some good sandwiches!
Amazing. Hands down the best sandwich I’ve had in DC. Girlfriend couldn’t finish hers, so I took it home and heated up the bread in the oven and the meat in a pan, just as good today! We’ll be back!

I dont know what happened to this place. It USED to be great..fresh bread, fresh everything but NOW...everythibg in the bag comes soggy, thrown together and not to mention very little, if ANY attention paid to what you ordered. Im terribly disappointed, this was once a good place for a good sandwich, but not anymore
Bomb! Best sandwich shop in dc. A bit on the pricey side but justifiable with the quality ingredients. Both the turkey sandwich  and the kale salad were great!! Can’t wait to try the cheesesteaks!!

Let me preface this: I am from the Philadelphia area and have a pretty high bar for certain types of sandwiches. That being said, I was very impressed with Grazie Grazie's product. We got an Italian hoagie (8-1), and a meatball marinara (nonna). The bread was fresh and had great texture and flavor, they were very generous with their meats, and the meatballs and marinara were flavorful and juicy. I try to come in with no expectations for hoagie shops to have an objective opinion, but found that here it wasn't necessary. If you are looking for a good Italian hoagie or meatball marinara sub, definitely come here. We will be back to try the roast pork. Update, ordered the cheese steak, and it was delicious. Good amount of meat and cheese, along with onions and my choice mushrooms.

Grazie Grazie has by far and hands down the best Subs in town.  The Forager is my favorite and every sub is uniquely crafted that makes you want to come back for more.  Their salads are also outstanding and are the perfect complement to the delicious subs.  My family looks forward to the days we bring Grazie Grazie home. Always a special treat.
Food was great but the customer service was awful. Employee #kg8141 did not greet us and acted bothered by our presence. Did not feel welcome at all.

so yummy. Big fan of the minelli..the cheese and those  sun dried tomatoes omg. love the cheesesteak without the bacon and my new fav the retzo. bravo <3  Also, to the people commenting about the cashier's not "smiling with their eyes" or being what they expect. show compassion...they're there to simply take your oder and make you a great sandwich. We're in a pandemic there are other things to worry about. you don't know what people are dealing with so to come take the time to write a comment about them when everything else was fine is ridiculous.
Their veggie subs are some of the best in the DMV! Huge and customizable.
Best Italian sandwich I’ve ever had. They don’t skimp on any ingredients. I got the Minelli, boyfriend got the philly special. Will be back!!
Would recommend the Retzo sandwich, the spicy honey adds just the right amount of heat. Skip the cheese steak sandwich, I have had much better elsewhere.
The Philly cheese steak with mushrooms was the best I've ever had! Thank you!

I grew up in Jersey, minutes from Philadelphia and surrounded by great cheesesteaks, sandwiches and Italian food. I have never found a spot that tasted just like home until Grazie Grazie. Food is amazing. Cheesesteaks taste just like from Philly. So. Good.

*COVID REVIEW*  I've been here only for the cannolis, which were pretty good. They had okay pandemic precautions in place, but the space is crowded in design so nobody visiting or working there was actually able to. maintain social distancing space.
Got a cheese steak, my girlfriend got a chicken wrap. Both were really good. Will definitely be back for the homemade sausage.
I like the sandwiches here, it's really good and taste amazing. Staff are very nice and very helpful.

the food is great to say the least. i just wish that the people making the sandwiches, would pay more attention to specific orders! i like my oil and vinegar on the side. and every single time i order i ask for oil, vinegar, and or dressing not to be put on my sandwich. but when i get the sandwiche it's always soaked in it no matter who's making it.
The food is really light and delicious!!! Due to COVID there aren't a lot people and the DC Warf is absolutely Beautiful!!!!
I ordered the ChaCha. It’s one of the most delicious, vegetarian sandwiches I’ve ever had! My only gripe is that the bread is tougher than I like for sandwiches, but it’s good!
People that think mangiolardos is a good sandwich need to come here.
Had Philly fries and they over filled me.
THE CHICKEN TENDERS WERE AMAZINGLY COOKED. THE PHILLY WAS HUGE AND VERY GOOD. MY DAD GOT TWO BOXES OF THE CHICKEN TENDERS, AND ATE THEM ALL.

Wow, terrific sandwiches!  I had the Retzo with grilled chicken and it was packed with flavor.  My husband had aba your own with roast beef and he raved about how good it was between each bite.  Super fresh ingredients, withgwith bread.  You wonder why only 4-stars??  The two times we have been there we have had the same cashier.  She is sullen and made us feel unwelcome.  Communication is a challenge with a mask, but she did not make any extra effort when we asked her to repeat something.  I almost felt like I had been naughty for not understanding something she said. There was no 'smile' in her eyes.  What a grump!

Grazie Grazie is the belove Taylor Gourmet brand reborn. It's a small single sandwich shop in the District Wharf by Dolcezza. There are a few seats inside and out, but during the COVID-10 pandemic, they offer delivery and safe pick-up.  Where they shine is with their appetizers and salads, surprisingly. Their risotto balls are killer! The sandwiches are hit or miss. The minelli sandwich is tasty, but the retzo was too much. The breaded chicken is deep-fried too much that it can give you heartburn as you eat it. Also, the sandwiches come on hard bread.  If you want the best sandwiches in D.C., go to one of these delis- 1) Mangialardo's on Capitol Hill, 2) Carl's Subbs in Woodridge, 3) Mother Rucker's north of H Street NE, 3) Bub and Pop's in Dupont Circle, or 4) MLK Deli in Congress Heights.
Good place to eat healthy , chickpeas salad the best. Thanks Rubén for your excellent service.
This is a awesome place to eat! I love it and the customer service is also awesome I would give more stars if I could

Decent if you eat meat. I try to eat vegetarian most of the time, and I appreciate that they have a couple of vegetarian/vegan sandwich options. Unfortunately, those options aren't very good, and sometimes they're not even both available. So this is a place I'm willing to eat if others want it, but I'd never choose it.

I loveeeee Grazie Grazie my Husband and I always get their sandwiches and delicious fries.  I live at The Channel right across from it. I went in for some fries and one of the cashier didn’t have her mask on while helping a customer and her mask was right on her chin very disappointed her attitude was 👎🏾. Other than that I love them, the owner is always nice.

COVID Update - Some staff are not wearing masks correctly (only covering mouth; not nose). Staff also not keeping the narrow entry area clear of waiting customers, eliminating any chance of distancing even for pickup orders.  ------------------------- Pretty good hoagies. Much better bread than its predecessor Taylor Gourmet.
Ordered the Minnelli today and it was sooooooo good. Can’t wait to try a number of other items off the menu!!
The Philly cheesesteak & the Rizzo were beyond delicious! Drooling just thinking about eating there again. The staff gleamed with kindness & went above and beyond to make us feel welcomed.
Great Italian subs. However if you are looking for falafel, go down the street to the falafel and hummus place. Otherwise, great Italian subs and friendly service.
Good chicken parmesan.

One of the best bangs for your buck around. I had a delicious oversized chicken parm sandwich and the risotto balls (arancini) that tasted like they came from a high-end Italian restaurant. Definitely recommend it.
Great subs and sandwiches! Fresh food served and excellent customer service.
Amazing food and great service. Can’t recommend enough

This place is very yummy. The sandwiches are huge and very filling and they are one of the few places that know how to do fries really well. And the chocolate chip cookies are divine. One of the best unique features is the manager is really sweet and friendly and makes sure you’re well taken care of. If you’re looking for a yummy, unique meal Grazie Grazie will surely satisfy.

Great place to eat before a show at The Anthem! Sandwiches were made to perfection and they don't skimp out on the meats as I was full after one. Most surprising was the roll itself as it held up but was even tasty on its own.

This is a fun little Italian inspired restaurant in the wharf area.  The menu options are a combination of light salad, sandwiches and vegetarian options.  The prices are very reasonable, especially for the view and relaxed fast casual atmosphere.
Great food. Went for lunch. Everything was fresh and quickly made to order. I also received a free cookie for my birthday lol
Salads are really good.

Finally, a good place to have a quick, filling bite before going to a show at the Anthem! I had the Luca sandwich and it was heavenly - the bread was delicious, the arugula was fresh, and the pickled onions were so sweet and salty. They have a lot of vegan and vegetarians options, too - I'm excited to try the vegan cheesesteak next time. I'm sure I'll be coming up with excuses to visit the Wharf now just so I can eat here again. It was so good!!
Good food, good vibes, sandwich flavor could have been better along with presentation. Staff was nice and location was clean.
Try the Philly.
Absolutely delicious food, fast friendly service, unique atmosphere.
Delicious sandwiches.
Taylor Gourmet’s spirit child
Good place to grab a sandwich on the go when your in the Wharf with fresh quality ingredients. Only downside is that sandwiches can be pricey.
The sandwiches here are very good. I like the Rizzo. Mozzarella cubes are also very tasty.  Very simple on the inside but clean and the staff are friendly.
Amazing sandwich and this was only half as it was split with a friend.  Grazie!   Lots of outdoor seating nearby to take in the Anacostia River vibe.

Awesome stop for a Sandwich. Vibrant and light atmosphere. Fresh ingredients and great tasting bread create fun combinations. Ordered the Rizzo on Italian bread and it's delicious. Will be stopping in again!
tasty and fullfilling salad and sandwich, super friendly service~😊
Dont come to this overpriced garbage sandwhich shop! I got the bird sandwich and my wife philly steak. They were both scrappled meat and tasted awful! My sandwich was awfully salty I barey could eat!
Hands down the best sandwich I've ever had. Not only was the food incredible, but the workers even gave me free cannolis and cookies!! Honestly, what else could you ask for?
Best sandwich  in DC
Highly recommend. Great sandwiches!
Love this place
1st time there, great sandwich,  I need more experiences to get that 5th ⭐

I had the Christopher salad here w/grilled chicken (subbed with Sherry vinaigrette for the dressing) and it was one of the best lunches I've had in a long time! Delicious, super fresh and very filling. The service was also great. I'll definitely be back!
We had the 8+1, the Benny, the cucumber salad and mozzarella squares. Everything was fresh and tasty. The salad was a little unusual, but I still liked it. Customer service was fantastic and fast.
Wow just WOW best sub shop I've come across in DC. The bread was amazing .

Love this place. It’s the best Philly cheesesteak in DC. The cheese squares are ridiculously good as well. If you’re a minimalist I recommend building your own cheesesteak the traditional way like Philly. Steak onions and wiz. I would say this is pretty comparable to a Philly cheesesteak if not better.

Loved this place. Located right on the boardwalk. They had some really cool designs and lighting. The cashier recommended the mozzarella sticks and they were delicious! We also had the chick pea salad and some fries. The fries were okay but the chick pea salad was so refreshing. Then we had some cookies that were sooo yummy- crispy on the outside edges but chewy in the middle. Just how I would make them at home. This is a great place to get some reasonably priced food. We actually loved their food better than those in The Anthem.

Hands down my new favorite sandwich and salad spot! You can't go wrong with a single menu item but I have to recommend the Columbus salad or the Philly Special!Aside from their amazing food, the service there is fabulous and the vibes the inside of the restaurant gives off are very rustic and relaxing.
One fantastic build-it-yourself salad! Great beef, fresh veggies, and one of the best vinaigrette dressings I've had in...maybe ever.

This resurrection of Taylor Gourmet is solid, with all the attention to sourcing of the sandwich components being the mainstay of a quality product. Definitely beats out the new "Taylor Gourmet" shops that seek to lure customers with the old name, but with inferior ingredients. Only complaint about Grazie Grazie would be that the layout inside is clumsy and makes getting in and out difficult. It also suffers a bit for the high price point, but given the location and quality of the sandwich, this is to be expected. Overall, a great sandwich shop worth visiting.

Foods really solid and that peppercorn ranch is insane. But of the 4 times I've been, 3 times they only had wheat bread, most recent time they didn't have bread at all. At a sandwich shop. At 730pm on a Friday
Amazing best service lady at the register was super nice and helpful eve I believe was her name thank you so much
Omg! So good! Philly's are the bomb! The Benny (chicken sandwich) was amazing!!!
This place is fantastic.  Very, very good sandwich.  Great service.  It’s what Taylor should have been
WOW- this was an AMAZING sandwich. I got the Minnelli. I had to wait longer than I would have liked for it, but once I got it I was blown away! So delicious.
Great sandwiches and helpful, quick service
Great food at a reasonable price.
Amazing sandwiches and salads.
Excellent restaurant with fresh ingredients with pre-created hot or cold subs or salads  as well as a create your own salad or sandwich option.
1st time there and steak and cheese was good

Went to lunch with a friend. We both got the Philly Special combo. I went to get my soda and no ice. The guy walking around said the machine broke that morning, but said he would give me a refund or do whatever I wanted. The line was long and they were getting busy.  I decided to just drink room temperature soda. Since they already knew that, it would have been much better if the person behind the register told the customer they had no ice. He seemed to be struggling enough as it was with just taking the orders. The sandwich was good sized. We should have just shared the sandwich.  My friend took half of her's home.  The sandwich was really salty though. I had to drink water all afternoon. Don't plan to go back.
Really good food. Greta price and amount of food for what you pay for. Pretty fast service too in a cool hip environment. The breaded chicken is good on a sandwich for sure.
This is such a great place to eat!  They have the best salads and sandwiches. The staff and the owner, Casey, are so friendly and professional. Definitely recommend this place!
Those sandwiches are DELICIOUS! The price is little higher than your average "hoagie" (sandwich), but you get what you pay in quality, quantity, creativity, and importantly - taste.
Better Philly Cheesesteaks than Philly... SERIOUSLY
Well-stacked, delicious sandwiches but will cost you for the convenience to the Wharf's view

Food here was good, got the giorgio I think thats how its spelled, split it with a friend after hitting our first bar.  Food was good, but price was location based clearly, not bad if you are hungry and in the area.

This is a new joint from an old friend. The founder of Taylor Gourmet got one of the shuttered locations and started Grazie Grazie. If you’ve been jonesing for Taylor, this will heal you. It may even be better! I like the Rendell, and my wife is glad that the falafel sandwich is back, now called the Cha-Cha.  But most importantly, you can still get your risotto balls!  Enjoying an Italian sub sandwich while watching the sun go down over the Wharf is not a bad way to spend a evening, IMHO.
So delicious!!!! Sandwiches are big enough to share. Love it!
Best kept secret in DC! Delicious sandwiches made with quality ingredients at reasonable prices get 8 thumbs up from this family of 4! We’ll be back!

I ordered tomatoes only on my sandwich for toppings, went back to work, and they added lettuce to it. I am allergic to lettuce.  I shouldn't have to check my order right there, and unwrap it for accuracy. It even says tomatoes on it with no mention on lettuce. I will currently not be recommending this place. I was order #42 AC2KQHU4AEAT in 8/22 @1156 am. Very dissatisfied.
Great tasting food and plentiful

I visited Grazie Grazie for the first time this weekend. I wasn't sure what to get but one the employes was super helpful in telling us all about some of the most popular sandwiches. I decided on an 8 X 1 italian sub. It was DELICIOUS. The service was friendly and fast as well. I will definitely be back!
We ordered the Lil Cs salad with grilled chicken and the risotto balls. Both were very good! The salad had really great flavor and the grilled chicken was delicious!
Best lunch on the wharf hands down.
Food was healthy and tasty
Loved Alan.

Ordered four different sandwiches.  All sandwiches were perfect.  The owner understands how to do it right.  The bread, meats, vegetables and seasoning were all spot on.  My favorite so far is the roasted pork with broccoli rabe....wow.  All sandwiches I would order again.  Sooo much better than the formula, boring chain restaurants.
(Translated by Google) An atypical way to order food, highly recommended  (Original) Una forma atípica de pedir comida, muy recomendable

Fabulous lunch place!  Food was excellent, and fair priced- for the neighborhood.  Not much more expensive than Subway, but in a completely different stratosphere, quality-wise. The Philly Cheese was exceptional!!!
Fantastic!
Great food Soda was amazing
Really excellent food at good prices in a fun space. One of the best sandwiches I've ever had! Great and needed addition to the Wharf.
Not easy to spot.
Very good deli style sandwiches in the Wharf District.
Sandwiches are great. You get your money’s worth. Love the shredded cheese.
Sandwiches are great quality. Happy to see this addition to the Wharf. Staff gave great recommendations.
Solid sandwiches that are easily big enough for two servings. Happy to have in the neighborhood.
Staffs are really nice! Their sandwiches and salad are amazing! Worth for the price 👍🏽
My new go to spot of the wharf!!! Definitely recommend the philly fries.
Just like Taylor Gourmet!
The Steak and Cheese gives Bub and Pop's a run for it's money
Four stars for fresh salad ingredients and "real" turkey. Five stars require complimentary bread and additional salad dressing or on the side; i could barely taste the dressing.
Hardest bread in the world

This is the spot for gourmet subs! Stopped by recently with some friends and we sampled everything. This is not your average sandwich shop. It's only quality ingredients and IG worthy decor here. Definitely check out the neon signs, wall graffiti and layout of the menus. We had the 9th, Minellii, Philly special and Forager. The Philly special is a must if you love cheesesteaks! The Minelli is packed with all types of meat and the veggies stuffed inside are delicious. The addition of the spicy aioli adds a bit of a kick.  I really enjoyed the food and service here. We had a fairly large order right when the doors opened. The staff and manager were great at accommodating us. Everything was really fresh and you can tell they take time with each sub. The baguettes themselves were great in texture. Tough and crunchy on the outside. Really soft and warm on the inside. Prices are reasonable considering its the Wharf. Highly recommend checking out the menu prior to stepping in or order ahead. I'll definitely be back to try some of their other vegetarian subs.
Amazing food, great service.  I thought I wasn't going to get much for the price, but I got a good deal for a ribeye cheesecake.
Back to basics.
Food and service were great. Philly Special is outstanding. My friends ordered the Loria salad and were very happy with it, too.
My favorite place to go after getting off work early! The Ingredients are fresh and flavorful. Try the Rizzo, the chicken with prosciutto is an unexpected but none the less delicious sandwich!
Super yummy - I've liked every sandwich that I've tried so far! Great lunch spot.
Short and to the point - DELICIOUS!! Well done, fair prices, I can't wait to go back!!
My sandwich was delicious and I am coming back to try the cheese steak!
We dined here twice during our stay. The food was ultra fresh and flavors on point. It was better than the fancy restaurants around. Wish we had a Grazie Grazie in my hometown.

As a Wharf resident and business owner, I was happy to see the spot open again. And they've done an outstanding job! Service is good, quality is terrific, and the sandwiches are tasty and huge. Definitely big enough to share. Definitely recommend, and hopeful for a long stint at a great location.

got the Philly special and it was amazing, I found no issue, I ordered another sandwich one of the cold one's and brought it to school for the next day after being refrigerated its still tastes amazing. It does have its similarities to Taylors but the vibe and menu are different and better, The menu is smaller and still has the best sandwich's from Taylors but they added some really cool ones too. overall had a great experience would 10/10 recommend

It's the exact same as Taylor Gourmet. The owner had to close and sell that chain, and for this location they literally just changed the name, it's the same menu. Not sure how that is going to work legally with this place and TG under new ownership using the exact same menu. The food is just OK, bread is hard as is the falafel (they call it chickpea fritters, but basically it's falafel). If you want falafel there is another place at the Wharf that makes it much better.
Hands down the best sandwich to hit my lips.  Ordered the Rizzo, place is also super cool and hip with its music and decor.

Hands down the best cheese steak I have ever had .  From Philadelphia, as you can imagine eaten my fair share ;-) Ordered the Philly Special, grassfed beef, cooper sharp cheese, spicy sauce, tomatoes, lettuce and onions.  The ingredients all came together in perfect harmony.  Cannot wait until my next visit.  Grazie!

Might have been one of the best sandwiches ever consumed.  It was called the Milelli.  Peppered Ham, Capicola with Proscutiio,  spicy Aioli, Arugula, Dried Tomatoes and fresh shaved Pecorino.  Spoke with the manager or owner for a moment, mentioned that EVERYTHING was made from scratch!  You can tell from the quality. I will be back to try the rest of the menu especially the grassfed ribeye cheese steaks, they looked devine.

I got the salad last week and it was great, exactly how it used to be when it was Taylor Gourmet. I am trying to avoid carb but today I ordered the Philly Special craving the steak and cheese they used to make. I ate half of it but I want to throw away the rest. The meat is horrible!!! I don’t know how I am supposed to chew and swallow that. I was happy to have my fav lunch spot open.. but this is very disappointing.  The only purpose why I am writing this is in case the owner/manager see and pay attention and make correction.
